begin_memory_text: At the beginning of the conversation he mentioned that he grew up on a farm working with horses. Because I've always been interested in horses we talked about that.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation he was asking me about school and we tallked about my degree. He was asking me what I liked about history and why I was studying it
end_memory_text: Towards the end we talked about traveling and going to different places all around the world. He has never been out of the country so he is fascinating by the prospect of doing so one day
rest_of_day_open: This week is going to be a super busy one. I am a graduate student and it is midterm week so I have a lot of grading that I have to do. Today is going to be busy as well because I have to go to work at Walgreens just to come back home and work my tutoring job
critical_positive: What worked well was that we both asked each other questions. We were genuinely interested in the things we had to say. We were both also pretty active listeners. I think in order to ask a real question you have to be paying attention to what the other person is saying and ask follow up questions about their life and stuff like that.
critical_negative: I dont really know that there are many things that didnt work. It never felt awkward, I never felt uncomfortable and even when it got to the end I was ready to leave but not because I felt like the conversation had come to a natural end but because I have to get my day started and am a bit tired

begin_memory_text: We talked about my experiences as a barn manager, horses, and how dangerous animals can be.
middle_memory_text: We talked about my partner's experiences in London and how strange people's expectations of life are.
end_memory_text: We talked about my thoughts on travel and Alex provided insight on how everyones travel experiences are different.
rest_of_day_open: My week will consist of me chasing income. I will spend time with my significant other and maybe will spend a night hanging out with some friends. I also have a dinner date with my significant others family. Still with all this considered there will probably be large sums of time not doing anything productive.
critical_positive: Alex knows how to keep a conversation going. She is interesting and is open to questions. I am a very good listener and I think that I can relate to people relatively easy. But overall it was Alexs' excitement for life that allowed for such an easy conversation to be had.
critical_negative: There were times when the video quality would lag.
